```console
kettle-jem
bundle exec rake kettle:jem:install
bundle exec rake kettle:jem:selftest
```

`kettle-jem` setup creates or updates `.kettle-jem.yml`, installs template
support, and runs the template workflow. `kettle:jem:install` reapplies
template updates. `kettle:jem:selftest` checks template drift in a temporary
workspace.

Useful runtime controls:

| Setting | Use |
|---|---|
| `KETTLE_JEM_VERBOSE=true` | Show detailed template output. |
| `PARSE_ERROR_MODE=fail` | Fail when an AST/parser-backed merge cannot run. |
| `PARSE_ERROR_MODE=skip` | Preserve the destination when parsing is unavailable. |
| `FAILURE_MODE=error` | Raise on merge failure. |
| `FAILURE_MODE=rescue` | Warn and keep unmerged content on merge failure. |
| `only=glob,glob` | Limit the template run to matching paths. |
| `include=glob,glob` | Add matching paths to the run. |
| `hook_templates=l|g|n` | Install local hooks, global hooks, or no hooks. |
